<article>
<h4>Rules for Roman Numerals/Roman System</h4>

<p>
1.	If a small roman numeral is behind a big roman numeral, the value of the small one 
will be subtracted from the value of the big one e.g.  
<b>IV</b> => 4, <b>IX</b> => 9, <b>XL</b> => 40, <b>XC</b> => 90, <b>CD </b>=> 400, <b>XD</b> => 490, <b>CM</b> => 900.
</p>
<p>
2.	If a small roman numeral is in-front of a big roman numeral, 
the value of the small one will be added to the value of the big one e.g. 
<b> VI</b> => 6, <b>CX</b> => 110, <b>LX</b> => 60, <b>MD</b> => 1500. 
</p>
<p>
3.	If the values are the same in 2s or in 3s, the values are added together e.g. 
<b>II</b> = > 2, <b>III</b> => 3, <b>XX</b> => 20, <b>XXX</b> => 30, <b>CC</b> => 200, <b>CCC</b> => 300 and <b>MMM</b> => 3000.
