<article>
<h3>6. Index Form</h3>
<p>
The plural of index is indices. 
Writing of a number in raise to power form is known as 
<strong>index form</strong> e.g. 
<br>
4 = 2x2 => 2<sup>2</sup> 
<br> 
8 = 2x2x2 = 2<sup>3</sup> 
<br>
81 = 3x3x3x3 => 3<sup>4</sup> 
<br>
18 = 2 x 3<sup>2</sup>  
</p>
<h4>Square and Square Root</h3>
<p>
<strong>Square</strong> of a number is the process of multiplying the number by itself e.g.  
<br>
Square of 3 = 3x3 = 3<sup>2</sup>  => 9
<br>
Square of <strong>3</strong> = <strong>9</strong>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Square root</strong> of a particular number is the process of determining a 
number that will multiply itself to give that particular number e.g.
<br>
Square root of <b>9</b> 
<br>
9  =  3 x 3  = 3<sup>2</sup>
<br>
Because, <b>3</b> in 9 has <b>power</b> or <b>index</b> of <b>2</b>, then the square root 9 is <b>3</b>.
<br>
<strong> The Symbol of Square root is √ </strong>
</p>


